  <slide>
    <title>Why is knowing about campuswide IT accessibility resources important?</title>
    <contents>
      <dl>
        <dt>Computing Labs</dt>
        <dd>Public computing and teaching computer labs have assisitive technologies available to students.</dd>

        <dt>Testing</dt>
        <dd>People testing websites and of software have access to assistive technologies for functional testing.</dd>

        <dt>Accommodating Faculty and Staff</dt>
        <dd>People may be interested for their own use or may know collegaues that may benefit from using some of these assistive technologies.</dd>
      </dl>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Windows: Ease of Access Options</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/Accessibility/" target="_presentation">Learn about accessibility options</a>
          <ul>
            <li>Stickey Keys</li>
            <li>Mouse Keys</li>
            <li>High contrast display settings</li>
            <li>Cortana voice control</li>
            <li>Magnifier</li>
            <li>Narrator</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Make sure to enable access "Ease of Access Features" on public computers</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

